Spring -> Spring is a Java based framework to built to create an
enterprise ready application.
When you create a java application there are lot 
more things that you have to do, lots of configuration
lots of property addition, lots of package and modules and jar 
file that you need to add to create your application.

Spring boot autoconfiguration ->
configure dispatcher servlet, bean object to json and vice versa, error mapping configuration

The request we get on the home page goes to the dispatcher servlet, it would be the one that will be handling the request first.
Dispatcher servlet is the front controller for the spring mvc framework

Knows all the mapping and the right controller to execute for which request

It uses the jackson conversion